<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED01FF83FF54FEDFFDA5FE64" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED01FF83FF54FEDFFDA5FE64" blockId="19.[151,1436,325,532]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FF54FEDFFEC0FE2B" bold="true" box="[199,322,361,387]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED01FF83FED9FEDCFD90FE2C" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1895" box="[330,530,362,388]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errans">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FED9FEDCFD90FE2C" box="[330,530,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Charippus errans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares some similarities in palpal morphology with 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED01FF83FBFFFEDCFB49FE2C" authorityName="Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[1132,1227,362,388]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yinae">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FBFFFEDCFB49FE2C" box="[1132,1227,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">C. yinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED01FF83FB48FEDCFAF0FE2C" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1243,1394,362,388]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heishiding" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FB48FEDCFAF0FE2C" box="[1243,1394,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">C. heishiding</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FAE8FEDCFF4AFE00" bold="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED01FF83FAE8FEDCFF4AFE00" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED01FF83FF6DFE38FEDDFE00" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[254,351,398,424]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="denjii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FF6DFE38FEDDFE00" box="[254,351,398,424]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">C. denjii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FEF5FE38FE3DFE00" bold="true" box="[358,447,398,424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED01FF83FEF5FE38FE3DFE00" box="[358,447,398,424]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but it can be distinguished by the not serrulate-edged LED and the long embolus coiled more than two circles (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED01FF83FE0BFE04FD9EFE64" box="[408,540,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 98–100" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[206,1388,194,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-19@20.[199,1388,181,1954]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 98–100. Palp of Charippus errans Thorell, 1895, holotype, in ventral (98), retrolateral (99) and dorsal (100) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500801" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500801/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Figs 98–99</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED01FF83FF54FE63FB11FE58" box="[199,1171,469,497]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED01FF83FF54FE63FB11FE58" blockId="19.[151,1436,325,532]" box="[199,1171,469,497]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED01FF83FF54FE63FEDBFE47" bold="true" box="[199,345,469,495]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Description.</emphasis>
See 
<bibRefCitation id="D11A2CAAED01FF83FE1CFE60FDC3FE58" author="Wanless, F. R." box="[399,577,470,496]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="81 - 172" refId="ref13444" refString="Wanless, F. R. (1988) A revision of the spider group Astieae (Araneae: Salticidae) in the Australian region. New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 15, 81 - 172." type="journal article" year="1988">Wanless (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. Habitus of male in 
